## Code Quality Standards

### Frontend
- Use TypeScript exclusively
- Use shadcn/ui components (check availability via MCP first)
- Handle loading, error, and empty states
- Implement accessibility (ARIA labels, semantic HTML)
- Mobile-first responsive design

### Backend
- Layered architecture (Routes → Controllers → Services → Models)
- NO business logic in controllers
- Validate ALL user input (Joi)
- Centralized error handling
- Comprehensive logging
- Input sanitization

### Both
- Consistent error handling
- Meaningful variable/function names
- Code comments for complex logic
- DRY principle
- Small, focused functions

---

## When in Doubt
1. Place documentation in `/docs`
2. Follow naming conventions
3. Include comprehensive examples
4. Keep documentation synced with code
5. Provide clear next steps for users

